## Key Concepts
| pre-configured environment | pre-built workspace.Delivered through an app. Provides specific functions, navigation, and knowledge objects.
| Splunk instance | Running splunk deployment/environment where users search data, manage apps and create knowledge objects.
| Roles | Determine what users can see and do. Splunk supports RBAC. Capabilities can be added/removed from roles. |
| Splunk Enterprise | Self-managed Splunk platform deployment ran by organizations in their own environment |
| User | Capable of seeing their own knowledge objects and those shared with them
| Power| Capable of creating,sharing knowledge objects with 'all users of an app, and performing real-time searches
| Administrator | Capable of installing apps, ingesting data and creating 'knowlege objects' for all users |
| Knowledge Objects | Events, tags, lookups, field extractions, workflow actions, and saved searches that help organize, enrich and make use of data. |
| Splunk Cloud | Splunk's managed cloud platform |
| Search and Reporting App | default interface for searching/analyzing data |  
| Splunk Bar | Appears on every page in Splunk. Used to switch between apps, edit account settings, view system messages, manage/edit configurations, monitor search jobs and find help |
| App Bar | Allows app navigation |
| Search Bar | Used to run searches by typing in a search string. |
| Time Range Picker | Used to retrieve events over a specific period of time. |
| Data Summary | Breakdown of the data indexed by host, source, and sourcetype. |
| Source | file, directory path, network port, script from which an event originated . |
| Host | hostname, IP address, or domain name of the machine from which the event originated. |
| Table Views | UI-driven way to explore and prepare data withouth using SPL
| Search History Menu | View and re-run past searches. Searches can be narrowed using the filter window. Show searches over various times(7 days to over 30 days)


## Write-up
- Splunk apps
  - pre-configured environments/workspaces
  - Sit on top of Splunk instance
  - extend pre-built knowledge/capabilities
  - solve specific use cases
  - launched/managed from the Splunk home page
- roles are what determine 'what a user is able to see, do, and interact with
- (3) predefined default roles in Splunk Enterprise
  - Administrator
  - Power
  - User
- sc_admin is the name of the Splunk Cloud admin role
- Splunk Cloud has additional Cloud-specific roles(token_auth and apps)
- Splunk Home allows users to explore, launch, manage Splunk apps, find documentation and set custom dashboards
- Admins/users(with appropriate capabilities) can add apps and data from the Home app.
- Splunkbase contains hundreds of apps
- "How to search" panel contains links to documentation 
- (8) main 'components of the Search and Reporting app's interface
  - 1) Splunk Bar
  - 2) App Bar
  - 3) Search Bar
  - 4) Time Range Picker 
  - 5) How to Search panel
  - 6) Data Summary
  - 7) Table Views
  - 8) Search History Menu


